go_data.justification: NDUFA10 is a subunit of mitochondrial respiratory complex I.
Most mitochondrial dGTP is tightly bound to respiratory complex I through the NDUFA10 subunit, indicating its mitochondrial location.
As a subunit of complex I, NDUFA10 is involved in cellular respiration.
Most mitochondrial dGTP is tightly bound to respiratory complex I through the NDUFA10 subunit.
